attributes.description_other:
It’s not new, it’s had a few owners and a few tasteful and suspect mods along the way. 
.
It's regularly serviced and maintained. I've chosen the best mechanic in San Francisco to do repairs and my philosophy is I'd rather pay the premium now than be stranded later. BUT It's 23 years old so please understand that hiccups may and do happen. 
.
It's good if you are somewhat mechanically inclined and willing to figure out problems if and when they arise.
.
Cruise control currently doesn’t work - I personally have found it ok without cruise control and would stress that the pedal is well weighted and doesn’t get too tiring. If it gets tiring then I suggest the van needs a rest also.
.
Cabin heat does not work. This is the heat that comes from the engine and out of the front dash. The heating core has been removed to prevent leaks, I only noticed after months of ownership. So bring a sweater/ warm jacket in case it's a little chilly during a morning/evening drive. The rear furnace DOES WORK, this is powered from the liquid propane tank and should only be used while you are camping.

attributes.description_included:
Sorry, but due to COVID-19, we are currently delivering this camper without any included accessories.  It will come fully fueled (diesel and propane), interior cleaned, exterior washed, batteries charged, fresh water-filled, and with dump tanks empty.  We ask that you bring all personal accessories, bedding, kitchenware, toiletries, playing cards, camping equipment, etc.

We expect that you will return the RV full of diesel and clean on the inside.  We will take care of everything else, including sanitizing for the next user.  We do not charge cleaning fees.

Delivery to an airport or any location within a 120-mile radius is available upon request (extra charge for this).
attributes.description_other:
We require a 14-day minimum rental, with a 10% discount if you rent it for at least 30 days.  

Small dogs welcome!  Please keep it to one pet per trip, though.  And pls keep in mind that if Fido chews through the Ultraleather, that's gonna be hundreds and possibly thousands of dollars to fix.  Just letting you know.

I don't have a bike or cargo carrier, but you are welcome to supply your own if it attaches via the 2" towing hitch receiver, for no extra charge.

Festivals and sporting events welcome.  No burning man.  No smoking.  No roof access.
attributes.description_recommendations:
We've taken this to luxury RV parks in SoCal (Newport Dunes is a favorite).  Taken it over to Arizona for Grand Canyon, Sedona, Monument Valley, and then up to Glen Canyon.  Maneuvering this rig across Hoover Dam was epic!

Most recently we did a trip East, camping in Tahoe, out through Utah to Dinosaur National Monument, then up through Jackson Hole to Grand Teton and finally Yellowstone!

Mostly campsites or RV resorts with the three kids.  But we don’t shy away from taking it to a hotel either.

attributes.summary: Few things are more satisfying, more soul enriching, or more fun than an epic camping trip. Even better? Taking one in a fully outfitted camper van! No more schlepping camping gear back and forth from the garage to your car. No more uncomfortable nights spent sleeping on the ground. GoCamp makes camping easy. We’ve packed it all in, so you can pack in the fun. Just bring yourself and a sense of adventure.
